HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 307
BY REPRESENTATIVE DANA HENRY
A RESOLUTION
To create the Expropriation and Acquisition for Strategic Transformation (E.A.S.T.) Task
Force to study the legal feasibility, procedural requirements, costs, and public
benefits associated with the feasibility of expropriating and redeveloping certain
vacant, blighted, or undeveloped properties in New Orleans East and to report its
findings and recommendations to the legislature by March 1, 2027.
WHEREAS, the area of New Orleans East, generally bounded by Lake Forest
Boulevard, including Jordan Road, Interstate 510, and the Inner Harbor Navigational Canal,
contains significant concentrations of vacant, adjudicated, and blighted properties; and
WHEREAS, over time, these properties have contributed to persistent issues
including illegal dumping, environmental degradation, diminished public safety, and barriers
to productive economic use; and
WHEREAS, fragmented and clouded property ownership, including heirs' property
and tax-adjudicated parcels, has impeded voluntary land assembly and coordinated
redevelopment in this area; and
WHEREAS, state law provides for the expropriation of private property for
constitutionally permissible public purposes including the remediation of blight, protection
of public health and safety, and development of infrastructure serving the public interest,
subject to the payment of just compensation; and
WHEREAS, any consideration of expropriation in this context must be undertaken
with appropriate safeguards including clear statutory authority, due process protections, and
a demonstrated public purpose consistent with state law; and
WHEREAS, the strategic location of the subject area, including proximity to major
transportation corridors and port-related infrastructure, presents potential opportunities for
economic development compatible with surrounding land uses; and
